# PROJECT TITAN - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values for local testing

# Telegram Bot Credentials
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
ADMIN_ID=your_admin_id_here
GROUP_ID=your_group_id_here

# How to get these values:
# 1. BOT_TOKEN: Message @BotFather on Telegram, create a bot, copy the token
# 2. ADMIN_ID: Message @userinfobot on Telegram, it will tell you your user ID
# 3. GROUP_ID: Add your bot to a group, then visit:
#    https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/getUpdates
#    Look for "chat":{"id":-1234567890} (negative number for groups)

# For GitHub Actions:
# Set these as repository secrets (Settings → Secrets → Actions)
# - BOT_TOKEN
# - ADMIN_ID
# - GROUP_ID
